ce:section.ce:para:
The proposed sensing platform was used to analyze both Cu (II) and risedronate sodium. Fig. 3
                            A exhibits that the emission intensity of carbon dots was decreased at 470 nm while that of the 2, 3-diaminophenazine was increased at 557 nm in the range of 0.02–55 µM. Fig. 3 B exhibited a linear plot between F557/F470 and concentration of Cu (II) with a linear regression equation of F557/F470 = 0.0097 + 0.0954 CCu (II) (R2 = 0.9986) with LOD (3.3 σ/S, σ is standard deviation of intercept and S is slope) and LOQ (10 σ/S) of 0.003 µM and 0.01 µM, respectively. The quantitative parameters of the sensing system were compared with other reported analytical methods (Table 1
                           ). It was found that the sensing system has widest linear range and lowest LODs than other reported methods, suggesting applicability of the sensing system for the determination of Cu (II) in real samples.
